  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For The GGF grant will be used to help the 200 member community in Ngarchelong to adapt to climate change by protecting their taro patches from rising sea levels and high wave surges. Taro patches are the main form of agriculture in Palau; they are located on low lying areas along the coast and are affected by salination. Families depend on taro farming for sustenance, and the loss of land threatens their livelihoods and food security. Ngarchelong Bngal a Klikm will work with women (primary caretakers of the taro patches) to implement a pilot project developed by the Palau Community College that uses a system of ditches and barriers to keep the salt water away. The group will distribute brochures on climate change and adaptation and mitigation strategies</narrative>
  </description>
